de.ityx.mediatrix.api.server

Interface ISCommon

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IControl, ISConnect
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ISAccount, ISAddress, ISAnswer, ISCase, ISCustomer, ISEmail, ISEmaillist, ISOperator, ISProfile, ISProject, ISQuestion, ISSingleMode, ISSubproject, ISTextObject

    public interface ISCommon
extends ISConnect, IControl
    The common interface contains basic functions e.g. for creating basic objects from the result set.

      • deleteAnythingWithIds

        boolean deleteAnythingWithIds(Connection con,
                            String statement,
                            List<Integer> ids)
                              throws SQLException
        Deletes the objects in the statement (table definition) e.g. Customers, Cases, Questions The objects are represented as a list with ids.
        Parameters:
        con - connection
        statement - statement The statement text must be defined:
        UPDATE SET geloeschtam = ? WHERE id IN (@) or DELETE FROM
        WHERE IN (@).
        No parameter and the place holder @. Because of constraints by the MSSQL the statement is cut into blocks with the length of 1000 ids.
        ids - ids
        Returns:
        boolean true if all objects were deleted.
        Throws:
        SQLException

        • writeLog

          boolean writeLog(Connection con,
               int operatorid,
               int questionid,
               int answerid,
               int action,
               String parameter,
               boolean operator)
                 throws SQLException
          Inserts an action in the operator log (e.g. complete or send actions).
          Parameters:
          con - connection
          operatorid - operator id
          questionid - the current question
          answerid - the current answer
          action
           - Action (e.g. 1=sent and complete, 2=requeued, 3=forwarded, 4=part answered , 5=completed , 6=opened, 7=canceled, 8=deleted, 9=stored, 10=call, 11=external forwarded, 12=new sent, 13=answer forwarded, 14=fax, 15=chat soft, 16=answer stored, 17=Rule, 18=Filter, 19=Info, 20=Account, 21=created, 22=stored, 23=released, 28=Checklist, 29=Keyword, 30=Splitting)
          parameter - a text
          operator -
          Returns:
          boolean true if the inserting was successful.
          Throws:
          SQLException
